column5: So the Mrs and I live in Gooderham and we're semi caught up (hahaha, far from it but took a break) and rolled down the hill to the lake.  Sadly no walleye or rainbow's were cruzing in close now that it's getting colder.  Just a SMB for the shore efforts in our hour.
Looks like a beautiful place. That's a nice mix of species too! Thanks for giving us a peek.
I had hopes of a walleye
